⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Ansel of Briarcliff
node M1 · M1 · ⟦Ansel of Briarcliff:M1:d7616d⟧

WHO   — Ansel of Briarcliff — the exile of the Flatlands
WHAT  — Celaena's friend and fellow trainee under the Mute Master — and her betrayer, a girl playing a long game to reclaim the Flatlands and her family's stolen seat of Briarcliff.
WHERE — M1 · Maas  Framework inputs: Throne of Glass — The Assassin's Blade  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a home torn away leaves a debt nothing but blood can settle; because grief left to rot turns to vengeance; because she would sooner be a traitor with a country than a friend without one.
HOW   — By charm and patience and the bladework of the Silent Assassins; by a poisoned cup, an alliance struck with Lord Berick, and a betrayal aimed at the Mute Master himself — and, when it fails, by flight.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Everything I did, I did for Briarcliff — and I would lose a friend a hundred times to win it home.

